final List<Map<String, String>> devotions2026AprilDecember = [
  // APRIL - 30 devotions
  {'date': '2026-04-01', 'title': 'Resurrection Life', 'scripture': 'Romans 6:9-10', 'body': 'For we know that Christ, being raised from the dead, dies no more. Death no longer has dominion over Him.', 'story': 'Easter reminds us that resurrection power is real. Xavier had been spiritually dead for years—going through motions, feeling nothing. Then he experienced Easter as more than a holiday. Christ\'s resurrection became his resurrection. He came alive spiritually. Resurrection isn\'t just a past event; it\'s available today.', 'thoughts': 'Christ\'s resurrection power is available to you. What area of your life needs to be resurrected?', 'action': 'Ask Jesus to resurrect one dead area in your life.', 'confession': 'Resurrect my dead places, Lord. I choose resurrection life. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-02', 'title': 'Living in Victory', 'scripture': '1 Corinthians 15:57', 'body': 'But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ.', 'story': 'Yara had been defeated by the same sin for years. She thought victory was impossible. Then she realized victory wasn\'t about her strength; it was about Christ\'s. When she surrendered to His lordship, victory became her reality. She wasn\'t defeated; she was victorious in Christ.', 'thoughts': 'Victory comes through Christ, not through your own strength.', 'action': 'Surrender one area of defeat to Christ\'s victory.', 'confession': 'Thank You for giving me victory through Jesus. I am victorious. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-03', 'title': 'The Power of Testimony', 'scripture': 'Revelation 12:11', 'body': 'They triumphed over him by the blood of the Lamb and by the word of their testimony.', 'story': 'Zeke was ashamed of his past. Then he realized his testimony—the story of his failure and Jesus\'s redemption—was one of his greatest weapons. When he shared it, people encountered Jesus. His shame became his strength.', 'thoughts': 'Your testimony of God\'s faithfulness is powerful. Don\'t keep it hidden.', 'action': 'Share your testimony with someone today.', 'confession': 'Help me to boldly share my story of Your faithfulness. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-04', 'title': 'Forever Love', 'scripture': 'Jeremiah 31:3', 'body': 'The LORD appeared to us in the past, saying: I have loved you with an everlasting love; I have drawn you with unfailing kindness.', 'story': 'Amelia struggled with the fear that God\'s love was temporary—that eventually He\'d give up on her. Then she encountered this verse. God\'s love wasn\'t temporary; it was everlasting. He drew her with unfailing kindness. Her fear of abandonment dissolved.', 'thoughts': 'God\'s love for you is everlasting. He will never give up.', 'action': 'Rest in the security of God\'s everlasting love.', 'confession': 'Thank You for loving me with everlasting love. I am secure in You. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-05', 'title': 'The Gateway of Praise', 'scripture': 'Psalm 100:4', 'body': 'Enter his gates with thanksgiving and his courts with praise; give thanks to him and praise his name.', 'story': 'Brandon entered God\'s presence through praise and thanksgiving. He found that praising God—even in difficulty—opened doors. His circumstances didn\'t change, but his access to God\'s presence did. Praise became his gateway to intimacy with God.', 'thoughts': 'Praise is your gateway to God\'s presence. Enter through it daily.', 'action': 'Enter God\'s presence through praise and thanksgiving today.', 'confession': 'I enter Your gates with thanksgiving and praise. Thank You. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-06', 'title': 'The Fragrance of Christ', 'scripture': '2 Corinthians 2:15', 'body': 'For we are to God the pleasing aroma of Christ among those who are being saved and those who are perishing.', 'story': 'Carly realized she carried something valuable—the fragrance of Christ. Without saying a word, her presence affected people. They sensed something different about her. She was living proof of Christ\'s transformation.', 'thoughts': 'You carry the fragrance of Christ. People sense His presence through you.', 'action': 'Be intentional today about carrying Christ\'s fragrance.', 'confession': 'Help me to be a pleasing aroma of Christ to others. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-07', 'title': 'Eternal Perspective', 'scripture': '2 Corinthians 4:17-18', 'body': 'For our light and momentary troubles are achieving for us an eternal glory that far outweighs them all. So we fix our eyes not on what is seen, but on what is unseen.', 'story': 'During intense suffering, Dakota struggled with perspective. She couldn\'t see how temporary troubles could matter. Then she shifted focus to eternal glory. Her suffering didn\'t disappear, but it was reframed. It was building something eternal—glory that would outlast her pain.', 'thoughts': 'Your troubles are momentary compared to eternal glory.', 'action': 'Fix your eyes on what is unseen—on the eternal.', 'confession': 'Help me to see my troubles in light of eternal glory. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-08', 'title': 'The Gift of Tears', 'scripture': 'Psalm 126:5-6', 'body': 'Those who sow in tears will reap with songs of joy. Those who go out weeping, carrying seed to sow, will return with songs of joy, carrying sheaves with them.', 'story': 'Ellie thought tears meant weakness. Then she realized tears were seeds. Her pain and sorrow, offered to God, became seeds of compassion, wisdom, and ministry. Years later, her tears had bloomed into a fruitful season of joy.', 'thoughts': 'Your tears can become seeds of something beautiful. Don\'t suppress them; surrender them.', 'action': 'If you\'ve been through pain, see it as seed planted.', 'confession': 'Take my tears and transform them into joy. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-09', 'title': 'Mercy Triumphs Over Judgment', 'scripture': 'James 2:13', 'body': 'For judgment without mercy will be shown to anyone who has not been merciful. Mercy triumphs over judgment.', 'story': 'Finley had judged someone harshly for their failures. Then Finley fell spectacularly. She desperately needed mercy. Remembering her judgment, she was terrified. But that person extended mercy. Finley learned: mercy isn\'t weakness; it\'s the ultimate power.', 'thoughts': 'Mercy triumphs over judgment. Choose mercy today.', 'action': 'Extend mercy to someone who has failed you.', 'confession': 'Help me to be merciful. Thank You for showing me mercy. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-10', 'title': 'Planted by Living Water', 'scripture': 'Psalm 1:2-3', 'body': 'But his delight is in the law of the LORD, and on his law he meditates day and night. That person is like a tree planted by streams of water, which yields its fruit in season and whose leaf does not wither.', 'story': 'Grace felt dry spiritually. Then she started meditating on God\'s Word daily—not as obligation, but as delight. She positioned herself by streams of living water. Her spiritual fruit began to flourish. She became a source of refreshment to others.', 'thoughts': 'Meditate on God\'s Word. Position yourself by living water.', 'action': 'Delight in God\'s Word today. Meditate on it.', 'confession': 'Help me to delight in Your Word and be refreshed by it. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-11', 'title': 'Humility Opens Doors', 'scripture': '1 Peter 5:5-6', 'body': 'All of you, clothe yourselves with humility toward one another, because God opposes the proud but shows favor to the humble.', 'story': 'Henry was successful, proud, and increasingly alone. His pride had driven people away. When he finally humbled himself—admitting weakness, asking for help—everything changed. People respected his humility more than they ever had his success. God showed him favor.', 'thoughts': 'Humility opens doors that pride closes. Clothe yourself with it.', 'action': 'Humble yourself about something today.', 'confession': 'Clothe me with humility. Help me to decrease so You increase. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-12', 'title': 'The Waiting Room', 'scripture': 'Isaiah 40:31', 'body': 'But those who hope in the LORD will renew their strength. They will soar on wings like eagles; they will run and not grow weary, they will walk and not be faint.', 'story': 'Iris was in a waiting season—waiting for a job, for marriage, for breakthrough. She felt like life was paused. Then she realized: waiting wasn\'t passivity. In waiting, she could renew her strength in God. As she waited hopefully, her strength was renewed, and when her breakthrough came, she was ready.', 'thoughts': 'Waiting can be a time of renewing strength. Hope in God during it.', 'action': 'Renew your strength while waiting on God.', 'confession': 'Help me to wait hopefully and renew my strength in You. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-13', 'title': 'The Dance of Faith and Works', 'scripture': 'James 2:22', 'body': 'You see that his faith and his actions were working together, and his faith was made complete by what he did.', 'story': 'James had faith in God but never stepped out. His faith remained incomplete. When he finally acted on his beliefs—took risks, served others, gave generously—his faith became complete. Faith and works danced together.', 'thoughts': 'Faith is made complete through action. Don\'t just believe; do.', 'action': 'Take one action that demonstrates your faith today.', 'confession': 'Give me faith to act. Help my faith be made complete. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-14', 'title': 'The Comfort of Presence', 'scripture': 'Psalm 23:4', 'body': 'Even though I walk through the darkest valley, I will fear no evil, for you are with me; your rod and your staff, they comfort me.', 'story': 'Kate faced her darkest valley. She felt God\'s presence tangibly—not removing the valley, but walking through it with her. His presence was enough. She wasn\'t comforted by the valley disappearing; she was comforted by His constant presence.', 'thoughts': 'God doesn\'t always remove dark valleys, but He walks through them with you.', 'action': 'Thank God for His presence in your valley.', 'confession': 'Thank You for Your presence in my darkest times. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-15', 'title': 'Love Covers Multitudes', 'scripture': '1 Peter 4:8', 'body': 'Above all, love each other deeply, because love covers a multitude of sins.', 'story': 'Leo kept detailed records of everyone\'s failures. He held grudges, brought up past mistakes. Then he understood this verse. Love covers—it doesn\'t keep score. When he chose to love others deeply, covering their sins, he freed himself. Love transformed him.', 'thoughts': 'Stop keeping score. Let love cover multitudes.', 'action': 'Cover someone\'s failure with love today.', 'confession': 'Help me to love deeply and cover others\' failures. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
