  {'date': '2026-04-17', 'title': 'The Strength of Gentleness', 'scripture': 'Matthew 5:5', 'body': 'Blessed are the meek, for they will inherit the earth.', 'story': 'Nathan thought gentleness was weakness. He approached everything aggressively. Then he saw a gentle leader accomplish more through quietness than Nathan ever had through force. Nathan learned: meekness isn\'t weakness; it\'s strength under control. The meek inherit the earth.', 'thoughts': 'Gentleness isn\'t weakness. It\'s strength under control.', 'action': 'Respond with gentleness today instead of force.', 'confession': 'Teach me gentleness. Help me to be meek, not weak. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-18', 'title': 'The Joy of Giving', 'scripture': 'Acts 20:35', 'body': 'It is more blessed to give than to receive.', 'story': 'Olivia had always focused on receiving—getting what she deserved, protecting what she had. Then she discovered the joy of giving. The more she gave, the more blessed she felt. She realized true joy came not from accumulation, but from generosity.', 'thoughts': 'Giving brings more joy than receiving. Experience it.', 'action': 'Give something to someone who cannot repay you.', 'confession': 'Help me to discover the joy of giving. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
