  {'date': '2026-04-26', 'title': 'The Calling to Maturity', 'scripture': 'Hebrews 5:12-14', 'body': 'In fact, though by this time you ought to be teachers, you need someone to teach you the elementary truths of God\'s word all over again. Anyone who lives on milk, being still an infant, is not acquainted with the teaching about righteousness.', 'story': 'Wendell had been a Christian for years but hadn\'t grown. He was still learning basics. Then he felt God\'s call to maturity. He studied deeply, served sacrificially, taught others. Growth was a choice. As he matured, he became fruitful.', 'thoughts': 'God is calling you to maturity. It\'s a choice.', 'action': 'Take one step toward spiritual maturity today.', 'confession': 'Help me to grow from infancy to maturity in my faith. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-27', 'title': 'The Mystery of Suffering', 'scripture': 'Romans 5:3-4', 'body': 'Not only so, but we also glory in our sufferings, because we know that suffering produces perseverance; perseverance, character; and character, hope.', 'story': 'Xander didn\'t understand why God allowed suffering. Then he saw the progression: suffering produced perseverance, perseverance produced character, character produced hope. His suffering wasn\'t pointless; it was productive. It was building hope.', 'thoughts': 'Suffering, when surrendered to God, produces hope. Trust the process.', 'action': 'Thank God for growth coming from your suffering.', 'confession': 'Help me to see my suffering as productive. Build hope in me. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
