  {'date': '2026-04-29', 'title': 'The Courage to Be Yourself', 'scripture': '1 Peter 3:3-4', 'body': 'Your beauty should not come from outward adornment...Rather, it should be that of your inner self, the unfading beauty of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is of great worth in God\'s sight.', 'story': 'Zara spent years trying to be someone she wasn\'t—dressing, acting, performing for others. She was exhausted. Then she understood: her beauty came from who she was on the inside, not the outside. When she stopped performing and started being, people were drawn to her true self.', 'thoughts': 'Your true beauty comes from within. Stop performing.', 'action': 'Be yourself today. Don\'t perform.', 'confession': 'Help me to cultivate inner beauty. I stop performing. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  {'date': '2026-04-30', 'title': 'The Invitation to Rest', 'scripture': 'Matthew 11:28', 'body': 'Come to me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest.', 'story': 'Aaron had been striving for so long. He thought rest was laziness. Jesus invited him to come and rest. As Aaron stopped striving and rested in Jesus, his burdens lifted. Rest wasn\'t weakness; it was strength restored.', 'thoughts': 'Jesus invites you to rest. Stop striving.', 'action': 'Come to Jesus and rest today.', 'confession': 'I come to You, Jesus. Give me rest. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},

  // MAY - 31 devotions
  {'date': '2026-05-01', 'title': 'The Beauty of New Beginnings', 'scripture': 'Isaiah 43:18-19', 'body': 'Forget the former things; do not dwell on the past. See, I am doing a new thing! Now it springs up; do you not perceive it?', 'story': 'Bella was stuck in her past—failures, mistakes, regrets. Then God invited her to forget what\'s behind and see the new thing He was doing. As she released the past, new possibilities emerged. God was doing something fresh.', 'thoughts': 'God is doing a new thing in your life. Release the past.', 'action': 'Release one aspect of your past. Embrace God\'s new thing.', 'confession': 'Help me to release the past and embrace Your new thing. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
