  {'date': '2026-05-03', 'title': 'The Strength of Weaklings', 'scripture': 'Psalm 10:17', 'body': 'You hear, LORD, the desire of the afflicted; you encourage them, and you listen to their cry.', 'story': 'Danielle felt powerless and small. Then she realized: God especially heard the afflicted. Her weakness was actually the place where she connected most deeply with God. Her powerlessness positioned her to receive His power.', 'thoughts': 'God especially hears the afflicted. Your weakness is your connection to His strength.', 'action': 'Cry out to God with your weakness. He hears.', 'confession': 'I come to You in my weakness. I know You hear me. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  
  // [Continuing with unique May devotions...]
  
